import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    airports_by_country = data.groupby('country').size().reset_index(name='counts')
    airports_by_country = airports_by_country.sort_values(by='counts', ascending=False)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(airports_by_country['country'], airports_by_country['counts'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Country')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Airports')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of airports by country?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.show()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['name_length'] = data['name'].apply(len)
    plt.hist(data['name_length'], bins=20, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['name_length'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['name_length'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['name_length'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['name_length'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Length of Airport Names')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airport names by length?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
from wordcloud import WordCloud

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    airport_names_by_city = data.groupby('city')['name'].apply(list).reset_index(name='airport_names')
    airport_names_by_city['airport_names'] = airport_names_by_city['airport_names'].apply(lambda x: ' '.join(x))
    text = ' '.join(airport_names_by_city['airport_names'].tolist())
    wordcloud = WordCloud(width=800, height=800, background_color='white', min_font_size=10).generate(text)
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 8), facecolor=None)
    plt.imshow(wordcloud)
    plt.axis("off")
    plt.tight_layout(pad=0)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airport names by city?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
